title: The.Assassination.of.Jesse.James.2007.Swesub.DVDRip-EXTREM-E
description: The last months of Jesse James&#039;s life, from meeting Robert Ford, a 19-year-old who idolizes Jesse, to the day Ford shoots him. Jesse&#039;s a wanted man, living under a pseudonym, carrying out a train robbery, disappearing to Kentucky, and reappearing to plan a bank holdup with Robert and Robert&#039;s brother as his team. The rest of the gang is dead, arrested, or gone from Missouri. Whenever Jesse&#039;s around, there&#039;s tension: he&#039;s murderous, quixotic, depressed, and cautious. Ford wants to be somebody and wants the reward. On April 3, 1882, things come to a head: Jesse is 34, Robert 20. Ford becomes famous, reenacting the shooting on stage, facing down the label "coward," shot dead in 1892.
